WEBVTT

00:00.158 --> 00:02.759
Previously on <i>The Secret Life</i>
<i>of the American Teenager...</i>

00:02.760 --> 00:05.140
Now, you've made
a lot of positive changes

00:05.141 --> 00:06.505
in the past
couple of months.

00:06.506 --> 00:07.672
And the next
positive change is

00:07.707 --> 00:09.574
that I want to
get pregnant again.

00:09.609 --> 00:12.444
You're trying to have a
baby to save a marriage

00:12.478 --> 00:14.546
that you never really
wanted in the first place.

00:14.580 --> 00:16.681
I just want some time
alone with my husband.

00:16.716 --> 00:19.251
But we don't have room for her.
Where would she sleep?

00:19.285 --> 00:20.619
We can all stay
at my parents' house.

00:20.653 --> 00:24.589
I would like you to go
ahead, and move out.

00:24.624 --> 00:26.324
And what if you had
gotten pregnant again?

00:27.260 --> 00:28.360
I know.

00:28.394 --> 00:31.263
You and I, we're not
friends anymore. Fine.

00:31.297 --> 00:33.465
Look, I know what you're here for.
What am I here for?

00:33.499 --> 00:35.634
And you know what, you can't have him.
Just check his phone.

00:35.668 --> 00:37.569
Adrian is still in love
with Ricky.

00:37.603 --> 00:38.670
I feel a little relieved.

00:38.704 --> 00:40.472
Well, would you feel
relieved if we split up?

00:40.506 --> 00:43.375
Maybe I could rent
Ashley's room from you.

00:43.409 --> 00:44.609
Maybe I could live here.

00:44.644 --> 00:46.511
Are you hiding something?
I'm not hiding anything.

00:46.546 --> 00:49.347
Which doesn't mean that you don't
have messages from Adrian.

00:49.382 --> 00:50.782
Either you trust me,
or you don't.

00:50.817 --> 00:54.719
<i>Aren't you bored just talking to?</i>
<i> Good night, Ricky.</i>

00:54.754 --> 00:56.488
What are you doing?

01:01.394 --> 01:03.361
It's been a week.
A whole week.

01:03.396 --> 01:06.298
It may be longer. I don't want to
be with someone who can't trust me.

01:06.332 --> 01:07.632
I thought you trusted me.

01:07.667 --> 01:10.402
I do trust you. I do!

01:10.436 --> 01:12.404
That's why
I stood up for you,

01:12.438 --> 01:14.272
I stood up for you when Karlee accused
you of trying to sleep with her.

01:14.307 --> 01:15.507
And yet, you didn't
trust me enough

01:15.541 --> 01:17.476
to know that if I have
messages from Adrian,

01:17.510 --> 01:20.278
they don't mean anything, they
don't mean anything at all.

01:20.313 --> 01:23.348
They were meant to be a record so if
you ever questioned why she called,

01:23.382 --> 01:25.283
or what she said
or anything else,

01:25.318 --> 01:27.385
I'd have some evidence
that I've done nothing.

01:27.420 --> 01:30.489
Did you see that I didn't
reply to any of that stuff?

01:30.523 --> 01:34.426
Ricky, please? Please just let
me come back to the apartment.

01:35.561 --> 01:37.462
I'll see you at school.

01:37.497 --> 01:40.499
No, I can't take it anymore, I can't.
I just can't.

01:40.533 --> 01:42.434
I don't think
I can come to school.

01:42.468 --> 01:44.302
Dad's taking John
to the nursery.

01:45.605 --> 01:47.639
Someone's at my door.
I have to go.

01:47.673 --> 01:49.508
Who is it, Adrian?

01:49.542 --> 01:52.277
If it is Adrian, I didn't
invite her over here.

01:52.311 --> 01:53.645
Tell you what, hold on,
and I'll tell you.

01:58.718 --> 02:00.352
It's not Adrian.

02:01.654 --> 02:04.256
No, it's not Adrian,
it's me.

02:05.391 --> 02:07.459
Long time.
How'd you find me?

02:07.493 --> 02:10.529
Phone app.
Find Ricky. It's new.

02:10.562 --> 02:12.664
And why'd you
want to find me?

02:14.634 --> 02:16.434
I think I might be
getting arrested.

02:16.469 --> 02:17.669
Arrested for what, then?

02:17.703 --> 02:19.437
You better not be
doing drugs or drinking.

02:19.472 --> 02:20.605
'Cause if you're
doing that stuff,

02:20.640 --> 02:22.240
I can't help you.
I won't help you.

02:22.275 --> 02:24.409
No, that's not
the problem.

02:24.443 --> 02:27.312
Oh, God.
Sex with an underage girl?

02:27.346 --> 02:29.481
I'm underage.
And, no, it wasn't that.

02:29.515 --> 02:31.283
What is it?
I don't have a lot of time here,

02:31.317 --> 02:33.218
and I've got
problems of my own.

02:33.252 --> 02:35.587
I sent a picture of my girlfriend
out to everyone on my phone list.

02:35.621 --> 02:37.422
What's wrong with sending a
picture of your girlfriend

02:37.456 --> 02:39.224
to everyone
on your phone list?

02:39.258 --> 02:41.259
She was in
a state of undress.

02:41.294 --> 02:43.662
Huh? She didn't have
any clothes on. Any.

02:43.696 --> 02:45.597
Why would you share
a picture like that?

02:45.631 --> 02:50.569
She's hot. And she broke up
with me, and I was angry.

02:50.603 --> 02:53.271
That was a really stupid thing to do.
For her.

02:53.306 --> 02:56.274
For you. Those kind of photos get
out there, you can't get them back.

02:56.309 --> 02:59.277
Any time anyone puts her name
into a computer in the future,

02:59.312 --> 03:00.579
that photo you sent out
could pop up

03:00.613 --> 03:03.415
when she applies to college,
or for a job, or...

03:03.449 --> 03:05.183
This is serious.

03:05.218 --> 03:07.485
Yeah, I realize that.
Her father already had it out for me.

03:07.520 --> 03:09.187
Oh geez, Ethan.

03:09.222 --> 03:12.524
I know, I know.
So can you help me out?

03:12.558 --> 03:14.259
You gotta be
over 18 now,

03:14.293 --> 03:16.528
you could be
responsible for me.

03:16.562 --> 03:19.698
And I got to get someone to
be responsible for me, and...

03:21.500 --> 03:22.634
This is a nice place.

03:22.668 --> 03:25.270
Uh-uh.
I can't. I have a son.

03:25.304 --> 03:27.439
I'm sure you've heard.
I had a baby with my girlfriend.

03:27.473 --> 03:29.241
They live here.

03:29.275 --> 03:31.610
They live here? Doesn't look
like they live here. You sure?

03:31.644 --> 03:34.346
Yeah, go in the other room, there
are toys and a bed, and...

03:34.380 --> 03:36.348
It wouldn't matter, I can't
be responsible for you.

03:36.382 --> 03:39.317
I don't think the authorities would
even let me, and I just can't.

03:39.352 --> 03:42.520
I have to take care of Amy and John, and
I'm going to college next year, and...

03:42.555 --> 03:45.290
Man, whatever.
Don't worry about it.

03:46.626 --> 03:51.496
Just go with me to turn myself
in, that's all I'm asking.

03:51.530 --> 03:52.631
That's all, huh?

03:55.268 --> 03:58.470
I'll go with you, okay? I just
have to make a phone call first.

03:58.504 --> 04:00.572
I'm gonna call my mom and
see if she can do anything.

04:02.341 --> 04:04.242
Did you have breakfast?

04:04.277 --> 04:06.678
No, I haven't had breakfast,
not for most of my life.

04:07.647 --> 04:10.315
Been there.
I'll get you something.

04:11.384 --> 04:12.550
Yeah.

04:12.585 --> 04:16.187
No, we're fine with
you staying here,

04:16.221 --> 04:18.456
if that's okay with George,
it's okay with us.

04:19.659 --> 04:24.362
You look strange.
You look happy.

04:24.397 --> 04:25.497
I am happy.

04:25.531 --> 04:27.565
No, you're not
a happy person.

04:27.600 --> 04:29.634
Not normally. Normally,
you're very serious.

04:29.669 --> 04:31.303
Maybe you're getting
sick or something.

04:31.337 --> 04:32.504
No, I'm not
sick or something.

04:32.538 --> 04:34.506
And, yeah,
sometimes I am serious,

04:34.540 --> 04:36.341
but I am a happy person.

04:36.375 --> 04:37.609
When?

04:37.643 --> 04:39.644
When I'm not dealing with
other people's problems,

04:39.679 --> 04:44.349
when I can just relax and
enjoy my husband and my home.

04:44.383 --> 04:46.685
Nah, that's not it.
I'm going with sick or something.

04:46.719 --> 04:51.523
Or maybe you're getting that empty-nest
syndrome women your age get.

04:51.557 --> 04:55.727
Women my age, huh? Well, if I got
anything, it's whatever the opposite

04:55.761 --> 04:58.563
of the empty-nest
syndrome is.

05:02.268 --> 05:04.536
You gonna answer that?
Ricky.

05:04.570 --> 05:07.339
Oh, I'm not talking to him.
Why not?

05:07.373 --> 05:09.541
'Cause he's not being
very nice to Amy.

05:09.575 --> 05:12.344
Are you not being
very nice to Amy?

05:12.378 --> 05:13.645
Who told you that?

05:13.679 --> 05:16.548
How many times do
I have to say it?

05:16.582 --> 05:19.250
I'm being nice,
and I'm going to be nicer.

05:19.285 --> 05:21.619
I'm going to talk to her
when I get to school.

05:21.654 --> 05:25.323
But before I can get to school,
I have one little problem.

05:25.358 --> 05:27.292
Remember that kid who lived
with us for a while?

05:27.326 --> 05:31.229
Ethan? The one that
everyone is looking for,

05:31.263 --> 05:35.266
because of that sexting incident?
Is he there?

05:35.301 --> 05:37.635
He's not here, but I
could probably find him.

05:37.670 --> 05:39.604
I owe you.

05:39.638 --> 05:43.308
Ricky, don't get caught up in
this mess. He is in serious trouble.

05:43.342 --> 05:46.511
Now if you know where he
is, you better tell me.

05:46.545 --> 05:51.349
And get your ass over here and talk
to Amy. She's been crying for days.

05:53.652 --> 05:55.487
What is that about?

05:55.521 --> 05:56.588
They broke up.

05:57.648 --> 06:00.148
