06:14.365 --> 06:16.365
So, according to the prenup,
you don't own the place,

06:17.939 --> 06:21.708
but my dad says that
you're out of college.

06:21.743 --> 06:24.711
Cable, utilities,
all that stuff included.

06:24.746 --> 06:25.946
That's not
in the prenup.

06:25.980 --> 06:28.849
I know, but my dad's feeling
very generous right now,

06:28.883 --> 06:31.184
and he knows that you'll be
starting college in the fall,

06:31.219 --> 06:36.056
and you can keep it, and everything in it
until you graduate.

06:36.858 --> 06:37.858
That's what he said.

06:38.092 --> 06:40.894
Wow. Uh...

06:42.897 --> 06:44.865
Do I have to give
you the ring back?

06:44.899 --> 06:47.734
No, you might want to move it
to the other hand,

06:47.769 --> 06:50.137
but, uh, no.
Keep the ring.

06:52.073 --> 06:55.042
So, friends?

06:56.010 --> 06:57.778
Sure.

06:59.113 --> 07:02.783
Even friends with benefits,
if you want.

07:02.817 --> 07:07.955
That's, uh, not an offer
I had anticipated,

07:09.724 --> 07:11.992
what with
with Ricky and all.

07:13.094 --> 07:15.862
But again, I loved you.

07:18.066 --> 07:21.735
And I loved you.
So...

07:23.738 --> 07:26.807
Who knows? Maybe some day
I'll take you up on that.

07:27.842 --> 07:28.909
How about today?

07:30.078 --> 07:32.112
We have to go to school.

07:35.083 --> 07:38.185
Come on, why would
you do that?

07:39.220 --> 07:40.821
You're in love with Ricky.

07:48.997 --> 07:52.245
Because we're friends,
and we're still married.

07:53.765 --> 07:55.212
We're married friends.

07:59.974 --> 08:02.809
So?
One for the road?

08:04.012 --> 08:05.946
I can't.

08:07.115 --> 08:08.949
We shouldn't.
Ah, why not?

08:13.154 --> 08:15.989
Amy, come on,
you have to go to school.

08:16.024 --> 08:17.589
Why do I have
to miss school.

08:18.188 --> 08:20.180
I can miss one day of school.

08:20.194 --> 08:22.162
I can't go to school
like this.

08:22.196 --> 08:24.898
Dad, I have been to school
every single day this week

08:24.932 --> 08:26.700
just to try to
talk to Ricky,

08:26.734 --> 08:29.136
and he still won't
talk to me, not really.

08:29.170 --> 08:32.806
He just wants more time
and more time.

08:33.941 --> 08:35.876
I screwed
everything up, Dad.

08:35.909 --> 08:37.144
You screwed
everything up?

08:37.178 --> 08:38.979
He's been hiding the fact that
Adrian's been calling him.

08:39.013 --> 08:40.847
He screwed
everything up.

08:40.881 --> 08:42.849
No, I had no right to check
his phone messages.

08:42.884 --> 08:44.985
No, you didn't,
but everyone does it.

08:45.953 --> 08:47.220
Everyone like who?

08:48.790 --> 08:50.757
I don't know.
Doesn't everyone?

08:50.792 --> 08:52.993
Do you?
Do I what?

08:53.027 --> 08:54.995
Do you sneak around and do you
listen to my phone messages,

08:55.029 --> 08:56.730
and Mom's and Ashley's?

08:56.764 --> 08:57.864
Your mom and your sister
aren't even here.

08:57.899 --> 09:00.700
You're not saying...
What? I pay the bill.

09:00.735 --> 09:03.837
Dad, I can't believe that you've
been listening to my phone messages!

09:03.871 --> 09:06.706
No, I haven't.
I don't know the password.

09:06.741 --> 09:08.008
But I mean the
text messages and emails,

09:08.042 --> 09:09.910
they're right there
on the phone.

09:09.944 --> 09:11.711
It hasn't happened
that many times.

09:11.746 --> 09:13.013
And, hey, you don't think Ricky
has ever checked your phone?

09:13.047 --> 09:14.748
Are you kidding?

09:14.782 --> 09:15.816
You think he hasn't done the
exact same thing you did?

09:16.150 --> 09:17.851
Why wouldn't he?

09:17.885 --> 09:20.887
Why would he? There's nothing on my
phone he'd be interested in.

09:20.922 --> 09:22.823
Besides, he's not
that kind of person.

09:22.857 --> 09:25.859
Yes, he is. Anyone can be that kind of
person under the wrong circumstances,

09:25.893 --> 09:27.694
or right... Whatever.

09:27.728 --> 09:29.096
No, not Ricky,
he wouldn't do that.

09:29.130 --> 09:32.833
Well, yes, he would do that.
He probably did do that. Ask him.

09:32.867 --> 09:36.036
No! He's already angry enough at me
without making him angrier.

09:36.070 --> 09:37.804
I'll ask him.

09:38.906 --> 09:42.008
You go to school,
I'll ask him.

09:42.043 --> 09:43.700
Why does anyone even have
emails or texts you wouldn't

09:43.725 --> 09:44.925
want anyone to look at?

09:45.079 --> 09:47.948
You know what they call emails and
texts in a courtroom? Evidence.

09:47.982 --> 09:50.117
Yeah.
Found out the hard way.

09:52.920 --> 09:55.188
Sure you don't want to take a
quick look just for reference?

09:55.223 --> 09:57.891
No. I don't.
How old is she?

09:57.925 --> 09:59.092
Sixteen.
How old are you?

09:59.127 --> 10:00.794
Fourteen,
but I'll be 15.

10:00.828 --> 10:03.063
I'll be in high school
next year, I hope.

10:03.097 --> 10:04.798
How long was this girl
your girlfriend?

10:04.832 --> 10:06.032
Three weeks.

10:06.067 --> 10:07.934
Oh, geez. She sent you
a picture like that when

10:07.969 --> 10:09.703
you'd only been
together three weeks?

10:09.737 --> 10:11.071
She sent it to me
the first week.

10:11.105 --> 10:13.974
You know, it's a status thing
to have a picture like that.

10:14.008 --> 10:15.909
She sent it to me
showing it to guys.

10:15.943 --> 10:18.812
Did she know you were
sending it to guys?

10:18.846 --> 10:21.715
I wasn't.
broke up with me.

10:21.749 --> 10:23.150
I was offended,
you know?

10:23.184 --> 10:24.718
You need some help.

10:24.752 --> 10:25.752
That's what I'm here for.

10:25.786 --> 10:27.787
Some professional help.

10:27.822 --> 10:29.990
As much as you get around,
you're like a professional.

10:30.024 --> 10:33.827
No, I'm not. And I've changed
a lot since you saw me.

10:33.861 --> 10:35.162
When did you last see me?

10:36.097 --> 10:38.832
Three years?

10:38.866 --> 10:41.134
What happened? Why'd you leave
our house? Refresh my memory.

10:41.169 --> 10:45.805
I stole something from the
house, a set of knives.

10:45.840 --> 10:49.209
Not steak knives, scalpels.
They belonged to the doctor.

10:49.243 --> 10:51.978
Oh, yeah,
I remember, antiques.

10:52.013 --> 10:53.780
What were you going
to do with scalpels?

10:53.814 --> 10:55.148
Are you kidding?
They were beautiful.

10:55.183 --> 10:57.050
I got hundred bucks
for them on the street.

10:57.084 --> 10:59.052
And what did you do
with the hundred bucks?

10:59.086 --> 11:00.187
Sneakers.

11:01.989 --> 11:03.890
They're gonna put
me in jail this time.

11:03.925 --> 11:05.225
You know they are.

11:05.259 --> 11:07.761
I don't know anything other than
you have to turn yourself in.

11:07.795 --> 11:10.764
If the cops are looking for you,
you have to turn yourself in.

11:10.798 --> 11:13.033
And you're still under 18, so,
hopefully, they won't put you in jail.

11:20.208 --> 11:21.741
Why aren't you at school?

11:21.776 --> 11:22.809
Why aren't you at school?

11:22.843 --> 11:24.177
I have a situation
I have to take care of.

11:24.212 --> 11:26.079
Oh, and what is that?

11:27.748 --> 11:28.882
Sorry.

11:28.916 --> 11:30.016
Get out here.

11:34.021 --> 11:35.088
Hey, she's hot.

11:37.000 --> 11:43.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

11:45.497 --> 11:47.365
Hey, wait up.

11:50.369 --> 11:52.170
I want to
apologize, okay?

11:52.204 --> 11:55.373
I admit I did call Grant and
Jack just to make you crazy.

11:56.308 --> 11:58.009
And I apologize.

12:00.212 --> 12:02.246
Well, at least you
didn't call Daniel.

12:06.151 --> 12:07.418
You didn't call Daniel?

12:09.355 --> 12:13.024
How did you even find him?
He's listed, geez.

12:13.058 --> 12:15.093
You would do that?
You would go after my new boyfriend?

12:15.127 --> 12:17.095
Well, there wasn't much point in
going after your old boyfriends,

12:17.129 --> 12:19.030
you don't really
care about them.

12:19.064 --> 12:22.033
And they turned me down.
Good.

12:22.067 --> 12:24.369
But I care about you, and I care
that you're just trying to hurt me.

12:24.403 --> 12:27.071
You told Amy that I was
trying to seduce Ben.

12:27.106 --> 12:28.940
That I was trying to trick him
into getting me pregnant.

12:28.974 --> 12:31.075
Yeah, well, you are,
or you were.

12:31.110 --> 12:32.343
No, I'm not.

12:32.378 --> 12:34.979
And Ben and I are
just friends now.

12:35.014 --> 12:36.914
Yeah, because now
you want Ricky back.

12:36.949 --> 12:38.950
And you told
Amy that, too.

12:38.984 --> 12:41.152
So what? You don't even care that
Amy has tried to be your friend.

12:41.186 --> 12:43.054
You're going after
Ricky anyway.

12:43.088 --> 12:44.989
I think that's horrible, Adrian,
that's really horrible.

12:45.024 --> 12:46.057
They have a son.

12:46.091 --> 12:49.327
Hey, hey, they broke up,
he's fair game.

12:49.361 --> 12:51.329
If not me,
it'll be someone else.

12:51.363 --> 12:53.231
What are you talking about?
They didn't break up.

12:55.167 --> 12:57.035
Where'd you hear that?
From Ricky.

12:57.069 --> 12:58.336
So you're talking to
Ricky?

12:58.370 --> 13:00.872
I talked to Ricky, yes.

13:00.906 --> 13:04.308
And, Amy is no longer
at the apartment.

13:04.343 --> 13:06.277
Well, that makes
me sad, really sad.

13:06.311 --> 13:08.846
It looked like everything was
going to work out for them.

13:08.881 --> 13:12.116
Yeah, it almost never does when two
teenagers have a baby together.

13:12.151 --> 13:16.854
But it could. It could if their friends
and family supported them, maybe.

13:16.889 --> 13:18.556
And that's the right thing
to do, don't you think?

13:18.590 --> 13:21.993
To support Amy and Ricky being together
as opposed to trying to break them up?

13:22.027 --> 13:24.162
I mean, it's difficult enough for them,
already, I'm sure, without someone

13:24.196 --> 13:26.898
intentionally trying
to break them up.

13:26.932 --> 13:28.052
You don't want to do
that, Adrian.

