she's going out with.

27:33.616 --> 27:35.450
I mean, who's she
going out with? Ben?

27:35.484 --> 27:38.253
No. Someone new.
Somebody that Grace's new boyfriend

27:38.287 --> 27:39.354
is fixing her up with.

27:41.624 --> 27:43.458
I saw that.
Saw what?

27:43.492 --> 27:45.293
It does bother you.

27:45.327 --> 27:47.428
You're going to go there again
after what I just said?

27:47.463 --> 27:50.498
Are you ever going to believe me when
I say I'm not interested in Adrian,

27:50.532 --> 27:53.568
or are you always going to be sneaking
around to see if you can catch me

27:53.602 --> 27:56.337
picking up my phone or listening
in on my conversations

27:56.372 --> 27:57.438
and all that stuff.

27:57.473 --> 27:59.374
Let me ask
you something, Ricky.

27:59.408 --> 28:03.244
You ever pick up my phone, check
my messages, my emails, my texts?

28:05.314 --> 28:08.516
Aha! So you've done the same thing
to me that I've done to you

28:08.550 --> 28:10.285
only you
didn't get caught.

28:10.319 --> 28:13.087
And there's nothing on my phone
that would even bother you.

28:13.122 --> 28:15.156
See, this is what
I'm talking about.

28:15.190 --> 28:18.393
We just can't trust each other.
Why even try?

28:28.319 --> 28:30.587
This isn't what I wanted
to be doing tonight.

28:30.758 --> 28:33.526
Well, she's on
the way over, so...

28:33.561 --> 28:36.362
So what? I just got finished
with my last final,

28:36.397 --> 28:40.400
and I was just going to see if you
want to come over and celebrate.

28:40.434 --> 28:43.436
Sure. But the more,
the merrier, right?

28:43.471 --> 28:47.440
Grace, come on. Tell her I couldn't
get in touch with him,

28:47.475 --> 28:50.510
tell her he has
a girlfriend or something.

28:50.544 --> 28:52.445
But that would be a lie.

28:52.480 --> 28:56.783
Well, kind of. Come on,
I promise. I'll find her a date.

28:56.817 --> 29:00.386
No. It has to be the date I found.
It has to be...

29:00.421 --> 29:01.454
What's his name?

29:01.489 --> 29:03.523
Dante?
<i>Yes, Dante.</i>

29:03.557 --> 29:06.493
Just come over, we'll talk
about it, we'll talk to him,

29:06.527 --> 29:09.729
see if he's even interested and
we can get a little alone time.

29:10.765 --> 29:13.399
Okay.
Okay, then.

29:13.434 --> 29:16.336
<i>I'll just ask Adrian to drop me</i>
<i>off so you can drive me home.</i>

29:16.370 --> 29:19.472
And if he happens to be at your
apartment when she drops me off, then,

29:19.507 --> 29:21.474
that would be great.

29:24.745 --> 29:28.515
It's T-bone. He'll come over for that.
You can thank me later.

29:28.549 --> 29:31.351
Wait, what? No.
I don't want him to come over.

29:31.385 --> 29:32.585
You've been wanting him
to come over all week.

29:32.620 --> 29:34.354
Nora brought home steaks
from the butcher shop

29:34.388 --> 29:35.622
so you would have
a reason to call him.

29:35.656 --> 29:36.656
Call him.

29:38.459 --> 29:40.326
Come on, Ames,
I'm doing this for you.

29:40.361 --> 29:41.561
No, you're not.
You're doing this

29:41.595 --> 29:43.496
so I won't be annoyed with
you for looking at my phone.

29:43.531 --> 29:44.764
I'm not gonna call him.

29:44.799 --> 29:47.433
He has looked at your phone,
hasn't he? You asked him?

29:47.468 --> 29:50.637
Yeah, I asked him,
and no, he hasn't,

29:50.671 --> 29:52.705
so thanks for the
suggestion.

29:52.740 --> 29:55.675
Oh, he's just not admitting it.
I'm going to call him.

29:55.709 --> 29:57.777
You may not be crying
now, but I know you,

29:57.812 --> 30:00.480
and there's going to be crying until
we get this whole thing wrapped up,

30:00.514 --> 30:02.749
so just call him.

30:02.783 --> 30:06.352
By the way, did you tell Mom
that Nora is living here

30:06.387 --> 30:08.521
or am I just supposed
to be hiding that?

30:08.556 --> 30:10.557
Why would I tell Mom
that Nora is living here?

30:10.591 --> 30:12.458
Because she owns the
house.

30:12.493 --> 30:13.693
I have the house until you and
Ashley graduate high school,

30:13.727 --> 30:15.428
and I'm done raising you.

30:17.398 --> 30:18.832
There better be something funny
in that textbook, young lady.

30:19.733 --> 30:21.534
There isn't.

30:21.569 --> 30:22.802
Then what's so funny, that
I'm raising you and Ashley?

30:24.471 --> 30:26.439
Dad, do you even know
where Ashley is?

30:26.473 --> 30:27.607
Yes, I know
where Ashley is.

30:27.641 --> 30:28.808
I talk to her every day.
And we text.

30:28.843 --> 30:31.811
We text and text and text.
You can check my phone.

30:31.846 --> 30:33.313
And where is she?

30:33.347 --> 30:34.614
She's in Florida.

30:34.648 --> 30:36.482
No, I knew that, I meant
where is she tonight?

30:36.517 --> 30:38.451
She and her friend are
starting a new job tonight.

30:38.485 --> 30:40.453
Uh-huh.
What kind of job?

30:40.487 --> 30:42.555
Some sort of
medical assistant.

30:42.590 --> 30:47.694
Yeah, what is Ashley qualified to
assist with in the medical field?

30:47.728 --> 30:50.763
I don't know, I didn't hire her,
but she's a very smart girl.

30:50.798 --> 30:54.534
Mmm-hmm. Smart enough
to get out of this house.

30:54.568 --> 30:56.469
I thought
you liked the house.

30:56.503 --> 30:58.338
You liked the house when
it was you and Ricky here.

30:58.372 --> 30:59.505
What is it you don't
like about it now?

31:02.743 --> 31:05.712
Oh, of course, me.

31:05.746 --> 31:07.480
I've gotten that before.

31:15.623 --> 31:17.824
Ashley, this experimental
test program is for people

31:17.858 --> 31:20.560
who have depression.
I'm not depressed.

31:20.594 --> 31:21.828
I've been
depressed before.

31:21.862 --> 31:23.696
You're jaded,
not depressed.

31:23.731 --> 31:27.500
Well, they're paying $500.
I could be depressed for $500.

31:27.534 --> 31:28.668
I guess I could be, too.

31:28.702 --> 31:30.436
Let's at least find out
what it's about.

31:33.540 --> 31:35.608
"This medication could
cause irregular heartbeat,

31:35.643 --> 31:38.678
"liver failure or could
even result in death..."

31:42.750 --> 31:44.684
I'm out.

31:48.589 --> 31:49.622
Feeling better.

31:53.360 --> 31:54.460
Ta-da!

31:55.596 --> 31:57.463
We walked
all around the block.

31:57.498 --> 32:00.366
I mean, the entire block.

32:00.401 --> 32:04.404
And John let me
hold his hand... Well...

32:04.738 --> 32:06.572
Hey, buddy.

32:06.607 --> 32:09.642
It's been such a good day for me.
I'm so happy.

32:09.677 --> 32:13.379
I've got a place to live
and a new job,

32:14.581 --> 32:17.450
and you and John,

32:18.519 --> 32:19.552
and your dad,

32:21.588 --> 32:22.655
and Ricky.

32:23.691 --> 32:25.358
Can't we call Ricky?

32:25.392 --> 32:26.459
Can't we please, Amy?

32:26.493 --> 32:27.627
Hi, Daddy.

32:29.630 --> 32:33.333
No, no! He doesn't trust me
and I don't trust him, and...

32:33.367 --> 32:34.701
Everyone deserves
a second chance.

32:34.735 --> 32:37.704
Or even a third.
That's what Leo says.

32:37.738 --> 32:40.473
Even if I call Ricky, it doesn't
mean he's going to come over here.

32:40.507 --> 32:42.642
You won't know
until you try.

32:42.676 --> 32:45.445
Why don't you call him?
It's your celebration.

32:48.615 --> 32:49.749
I don't want
to wait outside,

32:49.783 --> 32:51.784
I don't want to
play games, okay?

32:51.819 --> 32:55.521
Hey, John,
good to see you, buddy.

32:55.556 --> 32:58.391
Why don't you get Grandma to
play with you and Moose outside?

32:58.425 --> 32:59.425
Okay.

33:13.774 --> 33:17.643
I lied.
I've looked at your phone before.

33:17.678 --> 33:19.345
A couple of times.

33:19.380 --> 33:20.813
Not that it was worth
compromising my integrity for

33:20.848 --> 33:24.584
by looking at it
or lying about it.

33:24.618 --> 33:27.553
But I guess we were both wrong
not to trust each other.

33:27.588 --> 33:30.590
I just don't know how we do that if
we really don't trust each other.

33:30.624 --> 33:32.625
You don't trust me?

33:32.659 --> 33:34.727
That's just an excuse for not
wanting to be with me, Ricky.

33:34.762 --> 33:36.729
You know you can trust me.

33:36.764 --> 33:39.499
You know what?
You can just go home, okay?

33:39.533 --> 33:42.301
You don't get a T-bone steak
for this conversation.

33:42.336 --> 33:44.604
You can go home, and you can try and
figure out how we can live together,

33:44.638 --> 33:46.606
and still not be perfect.
Good night.

33:46.640 --> 33:48.374
Oh, no,
I'm getting a steak.

33:48.409 --> 33:50.576
I might eat it outside,
but I'm getting a steak.

33:58.786 --> 34:00.353
So?

34:00.387 --> 34:02.321
So it went nowhere.
She wants me to go home.

34:02.356 --> 34:04.457
But I'm hungry.
And you invited me to eat,

34:04.491 --> 34:06.426
so I'm eating,
then I'll leave.

34:06.460 --> 34:07.693
You know what
the problem is?

34:07.728 --> 34:09.462
The problem is
you're not married.

34:09.496 --> 34:11.731
Oh, yeah? Well, maybe your
problem is you're not married.

34:11.764 --> 34:13.599
Both parties have to want to
be married to be married.

34:13.634 --> 34:15.400
My ex-wife does not
want to be married.

34:15.436 --> 34:16.469
Does your girlfriend
want to be married?

34:17.804 --> 34:19.539
Do you want to be married?

34:19.572 --> 34:20.639
I just want to eat.

34:22.376 --> 34:23.609
Yes. Just not now.

34:24.710 --> 34:26.579
I know, I know.

34:31.376 --> 34:33.543
Well...
There's always going to be children

34:33.578 --> 34:35.379
who need your help,

34:35.413 --> 34:37.313
and you're always going to want
to help them, so...

34:37.348 --> 34:38.415
What can I say?

34:38.449 --> 34:42.286
Well, you can say no.
I can even say no.

34:43.388 --> 34:46.223
Since when, Margaret?
You're you.

34:46.257 --> 34:47.324
Should we go get him?

34:47.358 --> 34:50.360
Well, we can't
just go and get him.

34:50.395 --> 34:52.462
Unfortunately,
he has to go to court.

34:52.496 --> 34:55.232
Until then,
he's gonna be in juvie.

34:55.266 --> 34:57.200
Now, Ruben's trying
to work a deal.

34:57.235 --> 34:58.368
This is a serious offense,

34:58.403 --> 34:59.436
you can't send just go

34:59.470 --> 35:02.339
sending naked pictures
of people around,

35:02.373 --> 35:04.441
unless you're
both over 18,

35:04.475 --> 35:06.476
and then apparently
it's not a legal issue.

35:06.511 --> 35:08.345
But it should be.

35:08.379 --> 35:10.314
Maybe, maybe not.

35:12.450 --> 35:14.418
You text me a picture and
I'll text you one.

35:15.586 --> 35:17.220
Is that a yes?

35:20.358 --> 35:21.358
Nice ring.

35:21.392 --> 35:24.428
Oh, yeah.
It was my engagement ring.

35:25.396 --> 35:26.396
Oh, no.

35:26.431 --> 35:27.331
What, you're engaged?

35:27.365 --> 35:28.365
Well, right now, I'm
married.

35:29.367 --> 35:30.367
Interesting.

35:30.401 --> 35:33.403
Yeah, he just moved out.

35:33.438 --> 35:35.305
But you're still married?

35:35.340 --> 35:38.108
Yeah.
Well, we're getting a divorce.

35:38.142 --> 35:39.276
So, you...

35:39.310 --> 35:41.144
Don't have children.

35:41.179 --> 35:42.279
You guys want
something to eat or...

35:42.313 --> 35:43.413
You're still in
high school, right?

35:43.448 --> 35:46.116
Yeah, but I'm a year
older than Grace.

35:46.150 --> 35:47.217
I'm graduating
after summer school

35:47.251 --> 35:48.352
and then
I'm going to college.

35:50.221 --> 35:51.488
So why the divorce?

35:51.522 --> 35:55.192
Well, I'm kind of in love
with my old boyfriend,

35:55.226 --> 35:56.326
but he and this girl
had a baby

35:56.361 --> 35:58.261
and they were
living together,

35:58.296 --> 36:03.266
but they just split up and I think I
might want to try being with him again.

36:03.301 --> 36:05.135
Uh-huh.

36:05.169 --> 36:07.270
Maybe we should have given
them both a list of topics.

36:07.305 --> 36:08.505
I don't think she
actually dated that much.

36:08.539 --> 36:12.309
You know what,
I like your honesty.

36:13.211 --> 36:15.145
I really do.

36:15.179 --> 36:17.347
But if you're trying to get
back with your old boyfriend,

36:17.382 --> 36:19.149
what are you
doing here with me?

36:19.183 --> 36:21.184
Uh, I don't know.

36:22.353 --> 36:24.521
I thought it would
make him jealous,

36:25.356 --> 36:27.391
and I was curious.

36:28.393 --> 36:30.060
About?

36:30.094 --> 36:32.062
About whether or not Grace
actually knows any hot guys,

36:32.096 --> 36:33.363
besides that one.

36:33.398 --> 36:35.232
You know you can tell what
a person thinks about you

36:35.266 --> 36:37.200
by who they try
to fix you up with?

36:37.235 --> 36:39.236
You think so?
Yeah, I think so.

36:39.270 --> 36:41.271
All right, well, um,

36:41.305 --> 36:44.207
what do you think
people think about you?

36:44.242 --> 36:45.308
Well, they think
I'm good looking,

36:45.343 --> 36:48.278
because you're good looking.
Hmm?

36:48.312 --> 36:51.248
And they think I'm smart,
because you're smart,

36:52.250 --> 36:54.451
and they think I'm sexy,

36:54.485 --> 36:57.320
because, uh,
well, you are sexy.

36:59.223 --> 37:01.224
You know what, your
self-esteem is pretty high

37:01.259 --> 37:03.326
for someone going through a
divorce so early in life.

37:03.361 --> 37:05.328
Yeah, it is.

37:05.363 --> 37:08.298
That's why even though my old boyfriend
and this girl have a baby together,

37:08.332 --> 37:11.134
I still think
I can get him back.

37:11.169 --> 37:15.272
Not that I'm totally sure
I want him back.

37:15.306 --> 37:17.407
She'd take him away
from Amy just to see?

37:17.442 --> 37:19.342
We're trying to have
a conversation here.

37:20.378 --> 37:22.379
So, what's your story?

37:24.382 --> 37:26.550
Well, I've been
married three times

37:27.485 --> 37:30.220
and I got nine kids.

37:32.190 --> 37:33.256
Really?
No, I'm playing.

37:33.291 --> 37:34.458
I don't have nine kids.

37:34.492 --> 37:36.159
I was just trying
to top your story.

37:36.194 --> 37:37.360
Oh, yeah,
that's difficult to do.

37:37.395 --> 37:40.464
Yeah. Uh, no, actually, I'm
a sophomore in college,

37:40.498 --> 37:42.265
my brother's a senior.

37:42.300 --> 37:46.269
We live upstairs and I
got a full scholarship.

37:46.304 --> 37:48.405
The wildest thing
I've ever done?

37:48.439 --> 37:51.208
I don't know,
a couple of tattoos.

37:51.242 --> 37:53.276
Oh, I'd like
to get a tattoo.

37:53.311 --> 37:55.212
Tonight?
No!

37:55.246 --> 37:58.281
No, I don't even have one picked
out yet, or a place to get it.

37:58.316 --> 38:00.183
Oh, 'cause, I an, I was going
to take you to my guy.

38:00.218 --> 38:03.086
He does some really,
really good work.

38:03.121 --> 38:05.155
Oh, um, when I said
I don't have a place,

38:05.189 --> 38:07.324
uh, I meant on me.

38:07.358 --> 38:08.492
I don't know
where I'd put one.

38:09.360 --> 38:12.095
Oh, uh,

38:12.130 --> 38:15.232
well, uh, how about
we get up out of here,

38:15.266 --> 38:17.200
so I can get a better look
at the canvas, huh?

38:17.502 --> 38:19.169
All right.

38:21.305 --> 38:24.207
You guys,
tattoos last a lifetime!

38:27.345 --> 38:29.246
Nice work, Grace.

38:29.280 --> 38:32.082
At least it'll keep her
away from Ricky.

38:32.116 --> 38:34.251
Amy and Ricky
got into a big fight.

38:34.285 --> 38:36.253
Amy checked his phone out
and he caught her.

38:36.287 --> 38:40.257
Really? You can check
my phone out any time you want.

38:41.425 --> 38:44.194
No, it's okay,
I trust you.

38:44.228 --> 38:45.295
Do you?

38:45.329 --> 38:47.264
Or do you just not want
me to see your phone?

38:48.332 --> 38:50.200
No!

38:50.234 --> 38:54.171
No, you can see my phone,
if you really want to.

38:54.205 --> 38:55.438
It's okay with me.

39:07.318 --> 39:08.318
It's no one.

39:10.321 --> 39:12.455
Tell no one I said hi.

39:12.490 --> 39:16.359
It's Ethan. He's stuck in some juvie
hall room with some other idiot.

39:16.394 --> 39:18.295
All right, can we just
talk about this?

39:18.329 --> 39:20.263
Yeah, I've been trying to
talk to you for a week now.

39:20.298 --> 39:24.334
Yeah, I let this go on
way too long because,

39:24.368 --> 39:26.236
Amy, all my life,
no one has trusted me,

39:26.270 --> 39:29.206
and all my life
I wasn't trustworthy.

39:29.240 --> 39:31.208
I think I've earned
the right to be trusted.

39:31.242 --> 39:32.475
It would be easier for
me to trust you, Ricky,

39:32.510 --> 39:35.145
if you had just said, "Hey, you
want to listen to this message

39:35.179 --> 39:36.446
"I just got from Adrian?"

39:36.480 --> 39:39.049
instead of not saying anything or
saying you had listened to it,

39:39.083 --> 39:41.384
and then you erased it.
That was a lie.

39:41.419 --> 39:43.220
Yeah, I guess it was.

39:43.254 --> 39:45.255
And I shouldn't
have talked to her at all.

39:45.289 --> 39:47.157
I should have told you
when I heard from her

39:47.191 --> 39:49.192
and when I called her
back to talk to her.

39:49.227 --> 39:51.294
I'm sorry. I apologize.

39:53.464 --> 39:57.234
And hello, you've lied to me
before and I still trust you.

39:57.268 --> 39:59.269
That was different.
How was it different?

40:00.404 --> 40:02.339
I don't know.
Let me tell you.

40:03.307 --> 40:05.375
Because it was different.

40:05.409 --> 40:10.146
Again, no one has ever
trusted me, other than you,

40:10.181 --> 40:12.382
so when I got busted,
I felt humiliated,

40:12.416 --> 40:16.286
and I hated myself for letting
you down and I felt unworthy,

40:16.320 --> 40:18.321
and I just
couldn't say that.

40:19.390 --> 40:21.224
It was easier to be angry.

40:22.360 --> 40:25.262
I'm very comfortable angry
and being the victim.

40:25.296 --> 40:27.330
It's a lifelong process
to change that.

40:29.300 --> 40:31.268
Again, I'm sorry.

40:39.243 --> 40:40.277
I'm sorry, too.

40:42.213 --> 40:44.414
And thank you for telling
me that, for apologizing.

40:47.184 --> 40:51.388
Can we please, please go back
to the apartment now? Please?

40:55.092 --> 40:57.093
Ethan.
Just wanted to thank me.

40:57.128 --> 40:58.261
Ethan again?

41:01.399 --> 41:03.233
Oh, my God.

41:03.267 --> 41:05.368
Wait, is this the photo that
he got in trouble with?

41:05.403 --> 41:09.306
No, it's Adrian showing me where
she's going to get a tattoo.

41:09.340 --> 41:13.143
Okay, sooner or later, we've got to
get a sense of humor about Adrian.

41:13.177 --> 41:17.080
What's funny about her constantly,
relentlessly, trying to break us up?

41:17.114 --> 41:19.316
You left out nakedly.

41:19.350 --> 41:21.351
She's crazy,
you know that?

41:21.385 --> 41:23.420
I know that.
And I'm all done with crazy.

41:25.423 --> 41:28.325
You know
I can be crazy too,

41:28.359 --> 41:30.260
if that's what you want,

41:30.294 --> 41:31.361
if that's what you like.

41:32.396 --> 41:33.363
I can.

41:34.365 --> 41:36.232
If you're no
done with crazy,

41:36.267 --> 41:39.269
let me be crazy for you,
don't go to Adrian.

41:39.303 --> 41:42.172
Uh, you? Crazy?

41:42.206 --> 41:45.141
Oh, yeah.
I can be plenty crazy.

41:47.211 --> 41:51.181
In fact, why don't we, the two
of us, go get tattoos right now?

41:51.215 --> 41:53.083
Of what?

41:53.117 --> 41:54.184
Wedding bands.

41:54.218 --> 41:57.187
We're probably never
going to have real ones

41:57.221 --> 42:00.256
so let's go get fake ones
tattooed, that'll show Adrian.

42:00.291 --> 42:04.060
You need a little more
practice at being crazy.

42:04.095 --> 42:06.129
Maybe we'll start
with something else.

42:06.163 --> 42:07.297
I can be crazy.

